<p>I need to dynamically calculate the total number of descendants in an editable tree/hierarchy. I know how to watch items but not items of items. Here is a plnkr with the code: <a href="http://plnkr.co/edit/UMtTRPBV4zuzenOB3RxY?p=preview" rel="nofollow">http://plnkr.co/edit/UMtTRPBV4zuzenOB3RxY?p=preview</a></p>  <h2>index.html:</h2>  <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; &lt;html ng-app='app'&gt;  &lt;head&gt;   &lt;script data-require="angular.js@1.4.6" data-semver="1.4.6" src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/angular.js/1.4.6/angular.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;   &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" /&gt;   &lt;script src="script.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;/head&gt;  &lt;body ng-controller="exampleCtrl"&gt;   &lt;h1&gt;How do you do a recursive hierarchical calculation in Angularjs?&lt;/h1&gt; Item 1 has 5 descendants. How do I automatically calculate how many descendants an item has with Angular?   &lt;ul&gt;     &lt;li ng-repeat="item in items" ng-include="'itemView.html'"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;   &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/body&gt;  &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <h2>script.js:</h2>  <pre><code>var app = angular.module('app', []);  app.controller('exampleCtrl', function($scope) {    $scope.items = [{     'name': 'Item 1',     'numberOfDescendants': 5,     'items': [{       'name': 'Item 1:1',       'numberOfDescendants': 3,       'items': [{         'name': 'Item 1:1:1',         'numberOfDescendants': 0,       }, {         'name': 'Item 1:1:2',         'numberOfDescendants': 0,       }, {         'name': 'Item 1:1:3',         'numberOfDescendants': 0,       }, ]     }, {       'name': 'Item 1:2',       'numberOfDescendants': 0,     }, ]   }, {     'name': 'Item 2',     'items': [{       'name': 'Item 2:1'     }, {       'name': 'Item 2:2'     }, ]   }, {     'name': 'Item 3',     'items': [{       'name': 'Item 3:1'     }, {       'name': 'Item 3:2'     }, ]   }, ];   }); </code></pre>  <h2>itemView.html</h2>  <pre><code>{{item.name}} | Number of Descendants: {{item.numberOfDescendants}} &lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li ng-repeat="item in item.items" ng-include="'itemView.html'"&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; </code></pre>